<m:math>
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mtext> </m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mtext> </m:mtext><m:mn>2.0 </m:mn><m:mtext> m</m:mtext>
 </m:mrow>
</m:math>

 so that the total magnetic field at the coordinate

<m:math>
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mtext> </m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mtext> </m:mtext><m:mn>1.0</m:mn><m:mtext> m</m:mtext>
 </m:mrow>
</m:math>


 is zero. In what direction must the current flow in the second wire, assuming it is equal in magnitude to the current in the first wire? Explain.</para></problem>
